history.text: Have you watched Monsters University
Do you agree with the rating of 6.8 for the movie?
Yes I have multiple times, have you?
I would rate it higher than that I really enjoyed it
I did as well, I think it's a great movie, and my kids love it.
It has a lot of big names doing the voices. My grandson loved it two
Do you like John Goodman, that voices Sulley?
Also, who is your favorite character in the movie?
He is perfect for it. I find that the voices sometimes match the way the stars look
The music is awesome two. Randy Newman does a lot of the music for animation movies. Think he did Toy Story as well. Billy Crystal does a great job as well
Yes, I know there are a few voices similar.  The music is great for both of them as well!
I really enjoy how they make the animated movies now. They include some jokes for the adults
Me too, they really have been doing a great job.
Do you agree with any of the critical responses?
The plot is good two. Tiny little Mikey trying to become a scary monster.
I don't see anything about the little girl in the movie, on the page. She's a big part of it, too.
Yes they seem about right. It was a good balance in the movie. Also taught a good lesson.
I know I was looking for that as well she is a key part. Loved that they called her Boo
I thought it was really original, especially when it came out.
Yeah, I loved her part in the movie.
I liked the Scare Games and how it taught lessons on perserverance and confronting fears
The producers are good at hiding valuable lessons
Have you watched the Prequel, Monsters University as well?
I did, too.
I did I just loved all the characters. It was well done
Do you think it was a good setting story for Monsters inc?
I thought Monsters U was a good follow up to Monster Inc.
I can't remember where Monsters Inc took place. I get them kind of blurred together
I think it's the CDC?
